1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with computing similarity measures for curves on surfaces, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. 
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The concept of homology is used in game theory to study the structure of games, and this paper presents a similarity measure based on homology. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The algorithm presented in the paper involves computing minimum area homologies, which can be seen as a data structure for representing cycles on surfaces. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper uses linear algebra tools to compute the minimum area homology, which is a common technique in numerical analysis. 
5. cs.SG (Social and Information Networks) - The concept of homology is also used in network analysis to study the structure of complex networks, and this paper presents a similarity measure based on homology.
